fields.value: Interpolated moment-masked data (DHT08, DHT17, DHT31, DHT33, DHT36)

dsDescriptionValue.value:
This data was processed from the following 1.2 m surveys presented in Dame, Hartmann, and Thaddeus (2001):
https://dataverse.harvard.edu/dataset.xhtml?persistentId=hdl:10904/10027
https://dataverse.harvard.edu/dataset.xhtml?persistentId=hdl:10904/10019
https://dataverse.harvard.edu/dataset.xhtml?persistentId=hdl:10904/10047
https://dataverse.harvard.edu/dataset.xhtml?persistentId=hdl:10904/10049
https://dataverse.harvard.edu/dataset.xhtml?persistentId=hdl:10904/10052
all hosted at https://dataverse.harvard.edu/dataverse/rtdc.

The processing followed the interpolation scheme of Dame et al. (2001):
"interpolated. In each spectrum, <= 2 missing channels are filled by linear interpolation. In each spatial plane, single missing pixels are filled by linear interpolation, first in l direction, then b."
and the moment-masking scheme of Dame (2011).
